eb|url=https://www.herecomesthesong.com/single-post/2017/07/19/Amber-Mark-a-songwriters-desire-for-more-S-P-A-C-E|title=Amber Mark: a songwriter's desire for more S P A C E|last=Fanthorpe|first=Katie|date=July 19, 2017|work=Here Comes The Song|accessdate=December 4, 2019}}</ref> The album art features a photo taken by her sister, in which Mark is wearing a watch that reads 3:33.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://soundofboston.com/interview-amber-mark/|title=Interview: Amber Mark|last=Bedian|first=Knar|date=2017-10-07|website=Sound of Boston - Boston Music Blog|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref> Each song on the record represents one of the six stages of grief.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://earmilk.com/2017/05/15/amber-mark-shows-prowess-in-life-and-music-on-debut-333am-ep/|title=Amber Mark shows prowess in life and music on debut '3:33am' EP|last=Evans|first=Steph|date=2017-05-15|website=EARMILK|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref> The song \"Monsoon\" includes samples of her mother's voice, which she explained in an interview with [http://www.soundofboston.com Sound of Boston] as \"a video recording of me flying back to New York for the summer while we were living in Berlin. I wanted to make a video for my godmother from my mother. Hence why I\u2019m telling her that they don\u2019t speak German and that she needs to speak English. When she says she loves me that is from a more recent recording she made for me while she was in hospice.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://soundofboston.com/interview-amber-mark/|title=Interview: Amber Mark|last=Bedian|first=Knar|date=2017-10-07|website=Sound of Boston - Boston Music Blog|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref> Her mother, Mia, also influenced her fashion greatly and Mark elaborates on this influence in her 2017 interview with Vogue as the \"3:33am\" EP was just released. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/fashion-amber-mark-singer-style|title=Interview: Amber Mark|last=Bobb|first=Brooke|date=2017-05-12|website=Vogue|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018 she issued \u201cConexao EP\u201d that included her single \u201cLove Me Right\u201d.<ref>Kellman, Andy. \u201cAmber Mark: Biography, Albums, Streaming Links.\u201d AllMusic, www.allmusic.com/artist/amber-mark-mn0003576734</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ List of albums\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:9em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:24em;\"| Album details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''3:33am''\n|\n* Released: 12 May 2017\n* Label: Virgin EMI\n* Format: [[Music download|digital download]]\n|}\n\n===EPs===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ List of extended plays\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:9em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:24em;\"| Extended play details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Conex\u00e3o''\n|\n* Released: 3 May 2018\n* Label: Virgin EMI\n* Format: [[Music download|digital download]]\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n====As lead artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles as lead artist, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"S P A C E\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/fr/Amber-Mark-Space/release/10359066|title=Amber Mark - Space|work=Discogs|accessdate=December 1, 2019}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2016\n| rowspan=\"5\"| ''3:33am''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Monsoon\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Amber-Mark-Monsoon/release/10359099|title=Amber Mark - Monsoon|work=Discogs|accessdate=December 1, 2019}}</ref><br>{{small| (featuring Mia Mark)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Way Back\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Amber-Mark-Way-Back/release/10359152|title=Amber Mark - Way Back|work=Discogs|accessdate=December 1, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Lose My Cool\"<ref>{{cite 