o]]\n|Wholigans\n|music band\n|\n|<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.popmatters.com/review/187807-the-who-who-hits-50|title= Who Hits 50!|website= PopMatters|author= Justin Cober-Lake|date= 21 November 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Winner (band)|Winner]]\n|InnerCircle\n|music band\n|\n|\n<ref>{{Cite web|url= http://www.koreaboo.com/news/netizens-discuss-boy-groups-with-the-best-fandom-names|title= Netizens discuss boy groups with the BEST fandom names}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Winter Soldier (comics)|Winter Soldier]]\n|Winter's Children\n|comics/film\n|Alternative: Children of the Winter\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8k3Nw0Yyz-w|title=Captain America: The Winter Soldier Interviews -- Sebastian Stan And Anthony Mackie|last=Stan|first=Sebastian|date=1 April 2016|website=YouTube|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-13}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Wiz Khalifa]]\n|Taylors\n|musician\n|Named after Khalifa's favourite shoes, [[Chuck Taylor All-Stars]]\n|<ref name=\"atlantic\" />\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"X-Files\" |''[[The X-Files]]''\n|X-Philes\n|TV show\n|\n|<ref name=\"vulture\" />\n|-\n|''[[Xena: Warrior Princess]]''\n|Xenites\n|TV show\n|\n|<ref>[http://www.tvacres.com/fans_xenites.htm Xenites]{{Dead link|date=August 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, TV Acres</ref>\n|-\n|[https://xgaddavirx.bandcamp.com/ xGaddav\u00edrx]\n|Gaddavinir\n|music band\n|Translates to the friends of Gaddi.\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/search/top/?q=gaddavinir|title=The singer calling their fans Gaddavinir|website=Facebook}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Zayn Malik]]\n|Zquad\n|musician\n|\n|<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/6866132/zayn-malik-pillowtalk-acoustic-version|title= Zayn Malik Releases Acoustic Version of 'Pillowtalk'|website= Billboard|author= Colin Stutz|date= 2 March 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Yu-Gi-Oh!]]''\n|Duelists\n|anime/manga\n|\n|{{Citation needed|date=November 2017}}\n|-\n|[[Yungblud|YUNGBLUD]]\n|Black Hearts Club\n|musician\n|Fans got matching black heart tattoos on their fingers and then called themselves the black hearts club\n|<ref>{{Citation|last=SIDEWALK TALK POP|first=|title=YUNGBLUD Interview- love for Halsey, heartbreak club, teenage shenanigans|date=2019-07-09|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=emAksaeIy0U|volume=|pages=|language=en|access-date=2019-08-14}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Zendaya]]\n|ZSwaggers\n|actress\n|\n|<ref>{{cite web|url= http://hellogiggles.com/zendaya-new-name-fans|title= Zendaya's fans are called \"ZSwaggers,\" but she's looking for a new name|website= Hello Giggles|author= Kathryn Lindsay|date= 11 February 2016}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Honorific nicknames in popular music]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Fandom}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of nicknames|Fandom]]\n[[Category:Fandom| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{pp|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n[[File:\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8 \uc6d4\ub4dc\ud22c\uc5b4 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8\uc11c \u2018\u7f8e \uc80a\uc740 \uce35 \ub9c8\uc74c \uc0ac\ub85c\uc7a1\ub294\ub2e4\u2019 (43593313235).jpg|thumb|Persons in support of the group [[BTS (band)|BTS]] are seen viewing an [[advertisement]] to a marketing campaign which includes the group while waiting for a concert that includes the group.]]\nMany [[fandom]]s have their own names that distinguish them from other fan communities. These names are popular with singers, music bands, films, television shows, books, games, sports teams, and celebrities. Some of the terms are coined by fans while others are created by celebrities themselves.\n\nThe trend of giving a name to a fandom became more popular in the beginning of the 21st century with the invention of [[social media]], although such names were used much earlier. Some people consider the [[Sherlock Holmes fandom|Sherlockians]] (fans of [[Sherlock Holmes]]) and [[Beatlemania]]cs (fans of [[The Beatles]]) to be some of the oldest known examples.<ref name=\"atlantic\">{{cite web|url= https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2012/08/beliebers-directioners-barbz-whats-with-pops-fanbase-nickname-craze/260798|title= Beliebers, Directioners, Barbz: What's With Pop's Fanbase-Nickname Craze?|website= The Atlantic|author= Jason Richards|date= 7 August 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"sherlockians\">{{cite web|url= https://www.wired.com/techbiz/people/magazine/17-05/pl_brown|title= Scott Brown on Sherlock Holmes, Obsessed Nerds, and Fan Fiction|author= Scott Brown|date= 20 April 2009|website= Wired|access-date=12 March 2015}}</ref>\n<!--Entries MUST have citations to reliable sources to be included!-->\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+\n!Object\n!Fanbase nickname\n!Type\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! class=\"unsortable\" |Ref\n|-\n|[[2PM]]\n|Hottest\n|music band\n|\n|<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web|url= http://www.billboard.com/fan-army-bracket/|title= 2015 Fan Army Face-Off|website= Billboard}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[5 Seconds of Summer]]\n|5SOSFam\n|music band\n|\n|<ref name=\"billboard\" />\n|-\n|[[Adam Lambert]]\n|Glamberts\n|musician\n|\n|<ref name=\"atlantic\" />\n|-\n|[[Adele]]\n|Daydreamers\n|musician\n|Named after the song \"Daydreamer\"\n|<ref name=\"wire\" />\n|-\n|[[Aerosmith]]\n|[[Blue Army (Aerosmith)|Blue Army]]\n|music band\n|\n|<ref name=\"atlantic\" />\n|-\n|[[Ailee]]\n|Aileeans\n|musician\n|\n|<ref>https://mobile.twitter.com/angelicailee/status/229022202052370433?lang=en</ref>{{Better source|date=November 2017}}\n|-\n|[[Alan Walker (music producer)|Alan Walker]]\n|Walkers\n|musician\n|\n|{{Citation needed|date=November 2017}}\n|-\n|[[Alden Richards]] & [[Maine Mendoza]]\n|AlDubNation\n|actor\n|AlDub is a portmanteau of the names of two actors, Alden Richards and Yaya Dub (Maine Mendoza), from the Philippines noontime show ''Eat Bulaga'' segment entitled \"Kalyeserye\".\n|<ref>[http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/showbiznews/news/22189/aldub-recognized-by-guinness-world-records-as-record-breaker-in-twitters-10-year-history/story]